Mantoykas (or Mantoukas, in Greek Μάντουκας) it's a common surname in Cephalonia island at Ionian Sea. It comes from the village Mantoykata, some kilometeres north of Liksouri. The first Mantoykas who came at Chalkis, Evia Island was Charalampos Mantoykas (Or Mpampis) who stayed there and made his family. Now, this surname is common only in Chalkis, Athens and Cephalonia.